    <div class="container">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            At <strong>Skyward</strong>, we value your trust and are committed to safeguarding your personal data.
            This Privacy Policy describes how we handle information about our guests, hosts, and visitors
            when using our services, website, and mobile applications.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect different types of information depending on your interaction with Skyward:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email, phone number, billing address, government ID (when
                required).</li>
            <li><strong>Booking Data:</strong> Check-in and check-out dates, property preferences, transaction details.
            </li>
            <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, device type, browser version, and location data.</li>
            <li><strong>User Content:</strong> Reviews, ratings, messages between hosts and guests.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Facilitating reservations and providing customer support.</li>
            <li>Processing secure payments and refunds.</li>
            <li>Sending booking confirmations, reminders, and updates.</li>
            <li>Detecting and preventing fraudulent activities.</li>
            <li>Improving the Skyward platform through analytics and feedback.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>
            We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share it in the following circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>With <strong>Hosts</strong> and <strong>Guests</strong> to fulfill booking arrangements.</li>
            <li>With <strong>service providers</strong> such as payment processors and identity verification partners.
            </li>
            <li>For <strong>legal reasons</strong> if required by law, court order, or government request.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
            We use cookies and similar technologies to improve website functionality, remember your preferences,
            and deliver personalized content. You can manage cookies through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
            We keep your personal information only as long as necessary to provide our services
            and comply with legal obligations. Booking-related information may be retained for up to 7 years.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
            <li>Request corrections to inaccurate information.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your account and personal data.</li>
            <li>Opt out of promotional communications at any time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Security Measures</h2>
        <p>
            We implement strong security practices such as encryption, two-factor authentication,
            and restricted access to protect your data. While no system is 100% secure,
            we continuously work to strengthen our protections.
        </p>

        <h2>9. International Users</h2>
        <p>
            If you access Skyward from outside India, please note that your data may be processed
            and stored in India or other countries where our servers are located.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. When we do, we will update the “Effective Date” above.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            For privacy-related questions, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:support@skyward.com">support@skyward.com</a>.
        </p>
